Q5. Why is professional licensure important to you?

"Professional licensure helps protect the health, safety, and welfare of the public.  Professional licensure is also a lifelong process through which licensed professionals continue to stay current in their field.  Licensure is one of several ways that engineers and surveyors can better themselves and in turn improve people’s lives."

---

#### June 2025 Engineer Spotlight: Kayla Erickson, PE [...] "My high school geometry teacher advised a STEM club and I really enjoyed the creativity of the challenges I took part in through that. She always used to ask on the first day of class, “How do you touch the ceiling?”  and I like to think that engineering follows that similar concept; the end goal is clear, but there are a lot of different ways to get to that goal. As for Civil Engineering specifically, I ended up stumbling my way into the field as a happy accident. In high school, I was interviewed for my involvement in the STEM club and when asked about what type of engineering I wanted to pursue, I panicked and said “Civil”, with no actual idea as to what a civil engineer does.
